&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stripe Accounting Team is responsible for supporting all products at Stripe, consulting on accounting implications, and supporting teams&#39; ability to make informed strategic decisions. We are responsible for the accurate and timely recording of all business-generated transactions on our balance sheet and income statement. We operate in a fast-paced environment and collaborate significantly with cross-functional and international teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is seeking an Accounting Leader to join its world class accounting team to oversee Bridge, a Company Stripe is expected to acquire in January 2025. You would lead our efforts to help us scale Bridge for the future, as we support rapid growth in a fast-paced environment. The Accounting team is responsible for all aspects of the financial, statutory, and internal reporting processes; financial systems; internal controls; and business support. You would also leverage your technical expertise to quickly identify accounting implications and impacts to customers while advising and collaborating with team members cross-functionally to develop operational processes that help us scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounting operations at Bridge, including monthly and quarterly close activities, analytical reviews and financial reporting deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
