&lt;p&gt;As the global leader of Management Consulting Partnerships &amp;nbsp;you will drive Stripe’s engagement with management consultants, payment advisors and other firms who operate at the board and C-suite level. &amp;nbsp;These firms help the largest enterprise with their global business and transformation strategies including the development of new business models, including monetizing payments through marketplaces and platforms. Often an enterprises’ &amp;nbsp;financial infrastructure is the cornerstone of these transformations and legacy players are being challenged on their innovation ability in a crowded and rapidly evolving space. &amp;nbsp; Therefore, Stripe needs to continuously engage, educate and support a broad base of influencers to ensure they clearly understand the value and capabilities that Stripe brings to these initiatives, early in the process. &amp;nbsp;Ensuring that Stripe is included in the right consideration sets and that these partners have access to resources in Stripe in service of their users. The leader of this function will work to engage firms directly and via scaled mechanisms partnering with product, marketing and GTM teams. &amp;nbsp;The covered firms will include McKinsey, BCG, Bain, Glenbrook, CMSPI, EDG and similar, while also building a community approach with value-added payment consultants &amp;nbsp;around the world &amp;nbsp;Success metrics will include engagement and engagement metrics with managed firms and development of a purpose built program leading to &amp;nbsp;Stripe being a preferred/short listed provider of next generation commerce transformations and platform use cases &amp;nbsp;being recommended by these firms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Define and build a scalable program to engage these firms individually and broadly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Engage a prioritized set of &amp;nbsp;firms at their most Sr. levels to create thought leadership exchange and deep awareness of Stripe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Engage Stripe’s most Sr. leaders, bringing the right Stripe thought leaders into the engagement at the right time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Define Metrics for success, iterating overtime as we learn what works.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Engage Stripe field leaders and teams to educate and evangelize the programs and top firms influencing users. &amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Engage with Stripe marketing, analyst and industry leaders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;15+ years of experience leading thought leadership development &amp;nbsp;and executive engagements in enterprise technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;10+ years of payments and fintech experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong enterprise background delivering complex, innovative solutions at scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Experience building and leading, new and existing global programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Deep experience engaging and influencing firms like McKinsey, BCG, Bain, and boutiques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven experience with enterprise transformation programs where innovative technologies are at the core of the initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven ability to present and evangelize new products and solutions to executives (business and technical) and external audiences. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proven ability to lead complex cross functional global teams at the most Sr. levels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Industry experience with Retail, Media, Insurance, FSI, Automotive, Platforms, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining and implementing new business models.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start-up and early stage technology company experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Masters Degree in Business Administration.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Global GTM Operations team is responsible for overall productivity and effectiveness of the sales organization, partnering closely with each GTM function and across Stripe to drive initiatives and support the overall rhythm of the GTM business. Within GTM, the Alliances &amp;amp; Channels (A&amp;amp;C) team is at the forefront of working with partners, sales and our users to drive revenue and growth.You will collaborate with senior A&amp;amp;C leadership as a strategic, operations, and analytics business partner, as well as work with the broader GTM and GTM Operations team to shape and execute key initiatives and continue to evolve the operation of the business. Responsibilities include go-to-market design, resource planning, quota setting and management, sales process optimization and business analytics. You will also partner with key cross-functional stakeholders, including Sales Strategy &amp;amp; Operations, Finance &amp;amp; Strategy, Global Systems &amp;amp; Processes, and the Planning and Insights team to streamline and optimize our internal processes and deliverables (monthly business reviews, weekly forecasting calls, target setting and planning) and deliver transformational initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an A&amp;amp;C Operations Lead to join our GTM Operations team, specifically supporting the A&amp;amp;C function as a strategic, operations, and analytics partner. We are looking for someone who is innately curious and ready to dig deep into operational and performance processes, systems, and data to assess current performance, identify improvement opportunities, and provide fact-based insights that enable us to introduce improvements in order to simplify complex cross-organizational systems to improve efficiency and drive growth. We are looking for a self-starter who is passionate about their work, detail oriented, analytical and has demonstrated success dealing with ambiguity in a high-growth environment, and solving problems with limited oversight. And lastly, we are looking for someone who is comfortable both as a team leader and an individual contributor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key strategic partner to the global A&amp;amp;C team, continuously identifying areas for opportunity, and improving key processes across teams with multifaceted systems and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our Head of Alliances &amp;amp; Channels to build sound strategies that will scale the A&amp;amp;C team globally, while collaborating with your GTM Ops peers and the rest of the sales organization to make sure the plans are aligned with regional and functional priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the operational and reporting needs of the organization by defining and prioritizing requirements, working closely with cross functional partners to identify solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report key performance indicators (KPIs), trends, and deliver prescriptive recommendations to drive efficiencies and scale across the org&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute initiatives designed to optimize sales team efficiency and productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee implementation of enabling systems and tools, working closely with internal systems teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively resolve data quality, process, and policy adherence issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of sales or GTM operations experience in a similar industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience being a business partner with a GTM executive or similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SFDC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the sales cycle and previous exposure to GTM teams, and Alliances and Channels or GTM Partnerships organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for understanding systems of work and how to improve them through transformative and iterative approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem solving and analytical ability, with a track record of “test &amp;amp; learn” demeanor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task and work in cross-functional, fast-paced environments with the pressure of multiple deadlines, multiple partners / vendors, and complexity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and desire for working in a start-up environment, developing business infrastructure, and energetically scaling a high-growth business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in GTM Partner Strategy &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience at a growth stage internet or software company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working cross-functionally with sales teams and deep familiarity with sales operations and sales KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Global Alliances and Channels team focuses on building, supporting, and going to market with professional services firms including systems integrators, consultancies, and managed services providers. We also lead go-to-market initiatives with our strategic technology alliance partners such as SAP, SFDC, Adobe, commercetools, and others. Our team helps Stripe increase the GDP of the internet by ensuring users have access to the broadest set of solutions using the Stripe platform and the deepest set of technology and industry experts. At the same time, we work to ensure our partners and Stripe build large, mutually beneficial businesses together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Partner Program Lead, you&#39;ll drive and optimize Stripe&#39;s partner-sourced revenue initiatives, focusing on SI’s, resellers, SaaS platforms, and technology partners. You&#39;ll develop and implement co-selling strategies, innovative programs, and ensure consistent global execution of these initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your work will directly impact Stripe&#39;s ability to scale its partnerships and reach new markets. You&#39;ll collaborate closely with regional teams, Product, and Marketing to align our partner strategies with Stripe&#39;s overall business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement a formal co-selling strategy for SaaS platforms and strategic partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Value Added Solution Provider pilot program, shaping how Stripe works with key solution providers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategies to acquire new users and increase revenue through diverse partnerships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a clear ROI model for allocating resources to co-sell efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement consistent processes for partner engagement across the sales cycle while accommodating local needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage separate tracking mechanisms for different partner types (SaaS platforms, SIs, ISVs)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and evaluate potential new partners for co-sell opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a strong relationship with our SDR team. Stay abreast of changes that impact the partner leads process and proactively address potential issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in partner program development and management, focusing on co-sell initiatives&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of various partner business models (resellers, tech partners, SaaS platforms)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with ability to demonstrate return on investment for partner initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project management skills and ability to lead cross-functional, global initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinking with ability to identify and capitalize on new growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding communication and stakeholder management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with partner relationship management and sales tools (e.g., Salesforce, Crossbeam)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
