&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;APAC Demand Generation is a team of marketers and channel specialists that drive strategies to engage prospects and customers and generate demand for our prioritized solutions. We partner closely with global and regional Campaigns, Product Marketing, Field Marketing, Sales Development, and Sales teams to bring full-funnel campaigns to life, optimize performance, and drive business impact. Our team works across all customer segments, and at each stage of the customer lifecycle journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a business critical role at Stripe that will have a significant impact across our GTM organization. From striving to always better understand our customers to understanding the health of our business, you will help define and lead Stripe&#39;s startups, small businesses, and mid-market strategy. Moreover, you help realize this strategy through driving marketing activations, building creative new programs, and working with sales to ensure full-funnel alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the multi-channel, regional demand generation strategy and plan to grow pipeline for funded startups, small businesses, and mid-market companies across Asia Pacific in collaboration with global and regional marketers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with digital marketing experts to acquire and re-engage customers through a broad mix of paid media tactics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Land campaigns in conjunction with audience PMMs and global campaign leads to acquire and nurture leads at scale through digital content, paid placement, digital events, targeted nurture programs, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build or adapt compelling content, marketing assets, and thought leadership to address unique regional needs working with global and regional channel experts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a cross-GTM coalition including Global Marketing, Regional Sales, Sales Development, and Sales Operations to jointly navigate the marketplace and grow pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own key business and revenue metrics for startups, small businesses, and mid-market companies across the sales funnel while investigating business health issues such as conversion, lead quality, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally to define regional requirements as Stripe refines our marketing capabilities, MarTech stack, and lead management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look for innovative ways to reach and engage our users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a thought leader representing Asia Pacific as we grow across our campaigns and broader go-to-market at Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually optimize for efficiency, scale for growth, and prioritize for focus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years relevant experience running demand generation and scaled marketing campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of paid media tactics, digital marketing strategies, marketing automation, email marketing tactics, and lead management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working closely with Sales teams, including joint planning and execution, driving disciplined lead follow up, and earning trust as a strategic business partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Superb organization and project management skills and the capacity to manage multiple complex projects at once; you’re a master juggler and don’t let it get the best of you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical skills and the ability to craft actionable insights from complex data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track-record of building and executing programs with a wide range of cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B2B marketing experience owning a regional demand generation strategy across multiple countries, customer segments, and products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience marketing to larger mid-market companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience marketing to startups and small businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the payments, SaaS, and financial technology sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience standing up a new marketing capability or team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at a highly dynamic, high-growth tech company or consulting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Investor Relations (IR) team sits with the Finance organization and is a key component of Stripe’s long-term success. Our team is responsible for developing and managing Stripe’s equity capital markets activities. Our primary focus is effectively communicating Stripe’s business strategy and financial performance in order to cultivate long-term partnerships with our global investor base. We also design and execute equity transactions and advise Stripe’s leadership team on developments and trends in our industry and the capital markets. We operate in a fast-paced environment and collaborate extensively with cross-functional teams and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate to join our Investor Relations team. This individual will support core activities of the IR team and collaborate with cross-functional partners across Accounting, Communications, Finance &amp;amp; Strategy, Global Equity Management, Legal, and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional partners across Finance and other orgs to analyze financial performance and key business developments for use in investor communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the creation and distribution of routine and ad-hoc investor reporting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with shareholder engagement activities, including investor meetings, calls, and events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on industry trends related to financial performance and equity capital markets&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own day-to-day operations for the IR program, including cap table management and other core processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years of relevant experience in equity research or investment banking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to bring structure to ambiguous areas of opportunity and work independently in an unstructured, fast-moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building integrated financial models from scratch and analyzing problems and data sets to form actionable conclusions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to be flexible and comfortable with changing requirements and a “roll up your sleeves” mindset to get any job done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and organizational skills, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to build strong collaborative working relationships with cross-functional partners and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for capital markets and a working knowledge of US GAAP financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with high-growth technology or financial services companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with GSuite tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with financial research tools such as FactSet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the organization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide leveraged and usable infrastructure for Stripes to explore innovative, new products while concurrently extending secure, reliable and cost-effective mature business lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable Stripe product teams to rapidly build new products, and quickly iterate on existing products, to drive value for our users and Stripe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Stripe’s product teams a secure, performant, and efficient platform for creating and maintaining their products and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable Stripe’s engineers to build scalable applications with high speed, quality and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable Stripe’s largest users to scale their businesses on Stripe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may work on a wide variety of critical business areas including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local Payment Methods&lt;/strong&gt; - We are dedicated to optimizing payment experiences globally. As we are expanding our portfolio of local payment methods we are also ensuring seamless transactions tailored to regional preferences. LPM Engineering is the first team under Stripe’s Payments umbrella to establish a presence in the new Bucharest, Romania site, part of a phased expansion of the entire group’s presence here. You will have a unique opportunity to be part of a team that helps the unlocking of new markets and empowers businesses worldwide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Money Movement -&lt;/strong&gt; We provide the capabilities to move and store money efficiently and reliably by integrating with the global financial system. This team is core to Stripe’s business and internal teams rely on our platform and infrastructure to create valuable products and services that billions of people use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer Infrastructure &lt;/strong&gt;- We are responsible for making Stripe’s developers happy and productive. We work on tools, processes, and code refactoring to accelerate Stripe engineering as Stripe scales. You’ll collaborate closely with partner teams in Europe, such as CI Infra and CI Services, Test Environments and Frameworks, as well as partner teams based in the US who provide language specific tooling for Engineers who develop in any of Stripe’s supported languages (Ruby, Java, Golang, Python and more).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance Foundations&lt;/strong&gt; - Internal Controls Engineering owns systems and tools to measure and increase operational efficiency of all internal controls throughout Stripe. We build tools for owners of financial, business, and technology controls. We are part of a larger Compliance Foundations engineering organization, and work closely with our partner engineering teams to increase efficiency and predictability of compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Developer Toolings&lt;/strong&gt; - The team is responsible for accelerating Stripe’s developers and providing a positive experience. We work on tools, processes, and code refactoring to enhance Stripe&#39;s engineering as it scales.The team has three main areas of responsibility. Our mission encompasses optimizing day-to-day engineering work in regards to our QA infrastructure, advancing the capabilities of the Synthetics tool, and facilitating effective service-to-service testing. Through these efforts, we aim to improve the reliability of Stripe&#39;s systems and platforms, enhance the quality of deliverables, and ultimately foster a more efficient and innovative development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work on projects that span technologies, systems, and processes where you will design, build, test, and ship great code every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a great customer experience for internal and external Stripe teams using our infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in roadmap planning and prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver value through a strong collaborative approach with multiple customers and stakeholders across Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug production issues across services and several levels of the stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
