&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/financial-connections&quot;&gt;Financial Connections&lt;/a&gt; is building the world’s best and most seamless experience for allowing consumers to link and instantly pay with their bank account. Our flows are included in some of the most recognized consumer sites across the globe, like &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/newsroom/news/airbnb-and-stripe&quot;&gt;Airbnb&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/newsroom/news/stripe-and-uber&quot;&gt;Uber&lt;/a&gt;, which use Stripe for bank payments powered by Financial Connections.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be joining the Bank Connectivity team within Financial Connections. Bank Connectivity is building a backend platform to connect and retrieve data reliably from 10,000+ institutions across the United States. As an engineer on the Bank Connectivity team, you’ll be responsible for building highly scalable, highly available backend systems that allow us to connect to Financial Institutions platforms that may not provide, in principle, the level of reliability and availability our users need. You’ll work on integrating with new institutions, building abstractions that allow us to extend our footprint at a fast pace, improving our routing systems to pick the best available connections at any moment and help us build an operationally excellent product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with a wide range of systems, processes and technologies to own and solve problems from end-to-end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build and maintain highly scalable, highly available systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft new products and features that impact millions of people and businesses around the world&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with stakeholders across the organization such as product, data science, partnerships, legal, marketing, operations as well as 3rd party providers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute against both short- and long-term roadmaps. Make effective tradeoffs that consider business priorities, user experience, and a sustainable technical foundation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold our high engineering standards and bring consistency to the many codebases and processes you will encounter.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
