&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team: Atlas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With Atlas, founders can start a company in a few clicks, from anywhere in the world. We believe that startups are one of the most effective ways to solve the world’s problems, and we want to give founders a running start. Atlas helps founders incorporate and set up their company, get discounts for the internet’s best tools, and automate operations while feeling ambitious, smart, and assured. Our goal is to create more startups that get to product-market fit, fast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Atlas is a small but mighty team within Stripe that moves fast to make things better for founders. In the past year, we’ve automated 83(b) election filing, helped founders purchase their shares in a single click - no cash needed, and enabled founders to open a bank account and use Stripe payments even faster. We currently help 1 in 6 Delaware C Corps incorporate their companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop a team of founder-obsessed product engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the Atlas roadmap, working with Product and Strategy to prioritize, scope, and deliver product that solve problems for Atlas users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make Atlas a great place for engineers to work - building for and maintaining Atlas should be fun and sustainable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Atlas ships both quickly and reliably, prioritizing stability and observability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage simple and straightforward solutions to problems, and help the team scope work that they can ship incrementally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the voice of our user, the startup founder, encouraging engineers to talk directly to users and reframe problems from the perspective of our users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a culture of metrics and measurement. We’ve defined metrics that give us confidence we are solving problems for users, and we prioritize work that supports this.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a track record of leading teams that build excellent products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of engineering management and 10+ years of engineering experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have managed full stack engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care deeply about the user experience and take pride in building products to solve problems and delight users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prefer simple solutions and designs over complex ones, and have a good intuition for systems that will last and scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in a collaborative environment involving different stakeholder and partners: we work closely with designers, product managers, lawyers, and data scientists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a high quality bar, attention to detail, and you help your team deliver polished products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Startup experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with Ruby, Javascript/Typescript, React, and SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe builds economic infrastructure for the internet. We’re moving beyond payments and “up the stack” to help our users run their businesses more effectively. Issuing is developing new APIs to empower businesses to launch physical and virtual card programs. We aim to help businesses deploy novel use cases that rely on fully programmable payment instruments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Engineering Manager to lead the Issuing Authorizations Engineering team. You’ll be responsible for expanding and developing the team. You’ll drive pillar vision and roadmap. You’ll lead our coordination with product teams, operations teams, and other engineering teams at Stripe. We’re looking for a leader with a strong background in building scalable products. We need someone who is comfortable in a fast-moving environment with lots of moving pieces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be actively involved in strategic direction, product decisions, roadmap shaping for an emerging business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Iterate rapidly on features, tooling, and processes as we launch first versions of new products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving technical direction to work through tech stack evolutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our users and financial partners on a daily basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain APIs, user-facing experiences, services, and systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make and adapt prioritization and staffing decisions as the team, business, and user demands progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer solutions across systems such as core money-movement infrastructure, data pipelines, banking systems, and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow, develop, recruit, and hire for an amazing team of engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think of yourself as entrepreneurial and enjoy moving quickly on new, green-field products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You hold yourself and others to a high bar when working with production systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy working with a diverse group of people with different expertise. Almost every role at Stripe collaborates with some engineers, from Sales and Support in sharing feedback from our customers, to Legal and Accounting in supporting our systems for tracking money movement and reporting around the world&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of engineering management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of overall software development experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building new, diverse teams to tackle challenging technical problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing senior talent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
