&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Compute organization at Stripe manages the core cloud infrastructure that powers Stripe’s products and services. Our teams are responsible for managing Stripe’s server fleet, container orchestration, and deployments.&amp;nbsp; As an Engineer working with teams in&amp;nbsp; Compute, you will play a key leadership role in enabling Stripe’s infrastructure to power all of our products, globally and at scale. Your solutions will allow our business to scale and achieve a best in class price/performance ratio.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Orchestration team within Compute at Stripe is in charge of building the core infrastructure used by product teams to build microservices to support our business. This includes defining and driving the vision necessary to achieve best of breed scale and availability. We continuously invest in building new distributed services and scaling existing technologies while working with various teams to meet their current and future needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support a team of engineers focused on building the next generation of service platform at Stripe. In addition to helping define the roadmap for the next 3-5 years, you will be interacting with many other managers and their teams at Stripe, who rely on the Orchestration service platform to deliver stable and scalable services to our customers. You will work with a&amp;nbsp; team that is in charge of building the core infrastructure used by the product teams to build and operate microservices to support our business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
