&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engineering Manager, Payments Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s Payment Intelligence group is responsible for optimizing each of the billions of dollars of transactions processed by Stripe each year on behalf of our users, in order to maximize successful transactions while minimizing payment costs and fraud. Radar owns the technical stack that enables us to make critical real-time decisions to step-up or intervene on every transaction that Stripe processes. The team is home to domain experts on fraud and payments systems that work across the larger Payments organization to stay ahead of adversarial attacks, and to develop novel ways to improve Stripe’s payments performance. We’re hiring for multiple roles within Radar across our product platform and experience teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager you define a vision and strategy for your area, enable engineers to do the best work of their careers, and ensure your team delivers outstanding results in both technology and business outcomes. You’ll obsess over talent and be an active partner to recruiters to ensure your team is staffed with the people it needs to accomplish its goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with a team of talented engineers and product managers to solve payment fraud and risk challenges for merchant fraud teams and other Radar users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the roadmap and priorities for your team, and work with dependencies across the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead an engineering team in achieving a high level of technical excellence and stability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be deeply involved in new product and market launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the team does its best work and interfaces effectively with the rest of Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit, coach and develop engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to engineering-wide initiatives as a member of Stripe’s engineering management team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4 years of engineering management experience and 10 years of overall experience in the industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successfully led high-complexity teams, working in parallel on multiple high-impact areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work very well cross-functionally, and are able to think rigorously and make hard decisions and tradeoffs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive on a high level of autonomy and responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage a healthy work environment that’s both supportive and challenging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical background and hands-on experience in solving large scale and difficult technical problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading product improvements on critical, highly-reliable systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with enterprise SaaS customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in building technology solutions for fraud (or other adversarial challenges)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service Platform org is responsible for empowering teams to build highly reliable and performant services, backing our payment systems, fraud detection, and a multitude of other products. As an infrastructure team, you will build and expand the service frameworks to make complex systems easy to use, resilient, and scalable. We build powerful interfaces for engineers that depend on these systems—deployment, load balancers, web framework, databases, Kafka and Kubernetes—while keeping them highly available and performant. We’re looking for engineering leaders who can drive the technical vision of Stripe’s service infrastructure platform for thousands of engineers to use and build on top of, and thrive in a highly autonomous environment with many moving pieces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager within this organization, you will lead a team of engineers, collaborate with infrastructure and product engineering orgs, and advance service oriented architecture (SOA) adoption at Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage a team of talented engineers on the team, providing mentorship, guidance, and support to ensure their success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand user needs and pain points to prioritize engineering work and deliver high quality solutions that meet user needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the execution of projects, overseeing the entire development lifecycle from planning to delivery, while maintaining high standards of quality and timely completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with high-visibility teams and their stakeholders to support the Infrastructure’s key engineering initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on technical leadership (architecture/design, vision/direction/requirements setting, and incident response processes) for your reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with leaders across the company to create and drive toward the longer term vision of Stripe’s services roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a collaborative and inclusive work environment, promoting innovation, knowledge sharing, and continuous improvement within the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partners with our recruiting team to attract and hire top talent, and define the overall hiring strategies for your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience as an Engineering manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical enough to drive clarity with staff engineers about architecture and technical strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing teams that shipped and operated critical distributed system infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing engineering teams working on API design, abstractions, frameworks, or client libraries (e.g. building internal or external developer products).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works effectively cross-functionally and is able to think rigorously, communicate effectively, and make or coordinate hard decisions and tradeoffs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourages a healthy work environment that’s both challenging and supportive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills for different audiences (leadership, users, company-wide).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with a variety of common infrastructure platforms (databases, logging, event streams, metrics, caching, etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading partially remote teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing sustainable, in-house framework and abstraction ecosystems in large engineering orgs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building serverless platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing rigorous incident response processes and on call rotations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
