&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Globalization Platform team plays a pivotal role in ensuring that Stripe products are accessible and user-friendly for customers worldwide. This team is responsible for creating and maintaining the infrastructure required to localize our products and services across various languages and cultures. By joining this team, you will contribute to providing a seamless experience for users across the globe and help expand Stripe’s global impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Full Stack Engineer on the Globalization Platform team, you’ll develop frontend solutions for internationalization including tooling and libraries, directly impacting Stripe’s global expansion. You’ll shape the team’s frontend strategy, collaborate across the organization, and contribute to unlocking new markets. This role offers significant growth potential as you help drive Stripe’s mission on a global scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement frontend components for our globalization platform, focusing on creating an intuitive user experience for localization workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the maintenance and improvement of frontend libraries and components used across Stripe for globalization efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in creating frontend integration strategies, making it easier for other teams to incorporate localization features into their projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross-functional teams to implement globalization best practices in frontend development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in bug fixes and performance improvements for existing frontend systems related to localization and internationalization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop and maintain documentation for globalization tools and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to code reviews and collaborate with team members to maintain high code quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay informed about frontend technologies and internationalization trends, suggesting improvements when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
