&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EMEA is a significant part of our business and a strategic priority for Stripe. Our team is responsible for identifying and executing on a product strategy to win in the region. We build foundational, localized products for EMEA, including local payment methods and self-serve growth. We also work closely with other functional teams to bring new products to the EMEA market. We are responsible for the success of the region, and work closely with our go-to-market teams to marry what we build with what we sell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Head of EMEA product you are responsible for setting the EMEA product strategy and owning the product roadmap. You have a team of Regional Product Managers who sit in our most important EMEA countries, and will work closely with the Local Payment Methods and Global Self Serve team to build highly localized payments products. Additionally, your teams will work cross-functionally with other product teams, partnerships, and go-to-market to ensure the success of the region. This is a highly collaborative and cross-functional role, and part of your job will be to set up and run the right operating mechanisms to work across teams towards a common goal. You will also be the product representative of the region, meeting with users and partners. You will partner closely with our EMEA CRO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the long-term vision and strategy for EMEA product&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand our users’ needs by spending time with users and teams on the ground&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the Stripe product representative of the region, interfacing with our users and partners&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a team of highly independent and effective Regional Product Managers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our EMEA CRO to push forward important initiatives (as they relate to product) in the region&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work extremely cross-functionally with other product teams to bring products to market in EMEA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
