&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Solutions Architecture Team partners with our users to realize their full potential through the adoption of prescriptive solutions that drive their growth and success. We influence revenue growth across Stripe’s product portfolio, and collaborate with sales, support, product management, and Stripe’s executive team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Stripe, managers grow teams and inspire them to do outstanding work. We are looking for a motivated thought leader to help build and scale our Southeast Asia and Greater China Solutions Architecture team. This leader must be a driver who loves building teams and businesses. This role requires great interpersonal skills to work cross functionally, as a trusted advisor to our Sales, Partner and Professional Services teams, as well as with our Product Development and Marketing teams. Your influence can have a far ranging impact. Individuals applying for this role must be entrepreneurial and self-driven with a passion for breaking into markets and creating something new they can be proud of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute Stripe’s technical sales strategy in conjunction with Sales leaders, Marketing, Professional Services, GTM Partner team and Product Engineering.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build repeatable playbooks and define execution best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit, mentor, develop and inspire SAs to do the best work of their careers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence the mindset of CXOs, developers, architects and other technical decision makers, helping to shape their long-term architectural direction and scope roadmap for them to get to their target end-states.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the voice of our users and customers and influence product direction and priorities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Professional Services, Support Services and Product Engineering to manage the customer journey from technical discovery to technical win to successful adoption, value realization and expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive thought leadership through presenting at EBCs, industry events, developing whitepapers and reference architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop and contribute to sales campaigns, sales enablement and partner development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years technical sales leadership experience: recruiting and developing high performance teams selling technology solutions to enterprise companies, ideally in a SaaS or pay-as-you-go business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in technical sales or pre-sales roles, such as Solutions Engineer, Architect, or Consultant, with a focus on architecting pre-sales solutions and establishing best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with customers in Asia Pacific, including Greater China &amp;amp; Southeast Asian customers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of cloud-based solutions and the customer journey, from prospecting to revenue realization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical acumen encompassing APIs, distributed systems, databases, developer tools, and enterprise systems architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience working with a variety of technology stacks, from modern web applications to legacy ERP systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong people management skills with a passion for coaching and developing others to their highest potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills communicating and collaborating with both business and technical stakeholders at all levels within an organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The proven ability to work collaboratively with product management, product marketing and product engineering, you are seen as a trusted and objective advisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for evangelizing our capabilities and success on social media and other outlets to build brand preference and recognition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A self-starter who will take the initiative to develop programs for enablement and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high degree of passion, energy, drive and willingness to travel 50% of the time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;International experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Domain expertise in the payments space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to speak and read in Mandarin&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Workplace team’s mission is to create and support work environments that are welcoming, comfortable, and intuitive. These spaces are designed to promote collaboration, well-being, and productivity while adhering to the rigorous safety, security, and confidentiality standards required of a financial services company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Workplace Experience team comprises hospitality-focused professionals who directly shape the daily experiences of Stripes, visitors, and candidates across 20+ global office locations. This geographically dispersed team oversees facilities management, daily operations, and programs, including a culinary team dedicated to preparing nutritious meals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the Workplace Experience team, you will lead the group responsible for developing and managing global workplace programs that enhance the Stripe employee experience. These programs include Food, Onsites and Events, Environmental Health and Safety, and Facilities Management (FM) Programs. You will scale team-wide tools, resources, and processes while driving global operational alignment through policies, standards, and guidelines. This role reports directly to the Head of Workplace Experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead, coach, and motivate a distributed team and provide direction and performance management to foster team excellence and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the development and management of workplace programs, including Environmental Health and Safety, Food, FM Provider Programs, Transportation, and Onsites and Events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and scale tools, resources, and processes to support the Workplace Experience team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive global operational alignment through the creation of policies, standards, and guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design measurement frameworks and synthesize feedback to enhance programs and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain standards for conducting program and site-specific business reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build roadmaps and iterate on team goals and priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across the Workplace Experience team, Workplace pillars (e.g., Design and Construction, Real Estate Strategy), and cross-functional teams (e.g., IT, HR, Corporate Security) to align workplace programs with broader business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in current offerings and develop projects and programs to address them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and analyze key performance indicators to inform strategic decision-making and identify opportunities for improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in program management within senior workplace services or facilities management, preferably in a global, fast-paced, and growth-oriented organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead and manage a diverse team, fostering a collaborative and high-performing work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and problem-solving skills with the ability to prioritize and coordinate multiple initiatives simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of project and program management, with a track record of successfully bringing projects and programs to market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to engage effectively with stakeholders at all levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with workplace technology, sustainability practices, and trends in employee experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to Stripe&#39;s global office locations as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s People Systems team is a highly collaborative, cross-functional team that drives key support for the People organization’s technology. We work with many different teams at Stripe. We are nimble and flexible individuals that can wear many different hats. We don’t mind working through ambiguity and love adding organization to chaos. We believe that success is not defined by any one individual, but rather by the collective work of the entire team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, the HRIS System Administrator will support our People team, other internal business partners, and company management in the development, on-going maintenance, and operational and technical support of all aspects of the Workday HCM system. In addition, this person is expected to participate in design and discovery of new solutions and take a critical role driving the implementation, user acceptance testing, deployment and technical documentation of key Workday projects that leverage the Workday platform or related third-party vendor applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver long-term improvement projects to ensure compatibility with the company’s evolving business applications landscape and needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the Workday HCM system expert and primary point-of-contact for day-to-day support of business processes, integrations, reporting, and dashboards to ensure consistent, high-quality business operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our People team and other internal stakeholders to help them define solutions using Workday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive technical requirements, implement, test, and deploy additional Workday modules as needed to support changes to business processes, or integrations as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and testing for Workday system updates or upgrades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify system gaps and deficiencies, and if applicable, suggest best practices or process improvements to help fill those gaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
