&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be an indirect tax subject matter expert (global VAT/GST) and resource to our business and finance teams in Stripe, managing aspects of our indirect tax planning, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Stripe’s expansion internationally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in policy matters affecting indirect taxes internationally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the international indirect tax compliance leads, and the international accounting teams on VAT/GST compliance, assisting with the ongoing enhancement of the indirect tax compliance processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting management of indirect tax audits and other indirect tax matters involving tax authorities internationally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other tax team members and product and engineering teams to help define requirements and collaborate on the design of tax solutions for our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote indirect tax awareness and knowledge including training and liaising with business and tax partners on changes to indirect tax legislation, systems, policies and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+&amp;nbsp; years of relevant indirect tax knowledge, laws and regulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree and professional qualification in tax or law&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous in-house experience within a multinational business and either legal or accountancy firm experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with indirect taxes as it relates to the distribution of digital services and physical products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounting experience and proficiency with ERP systems and related data analytics skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to clearly and concisely interface with all levels of management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management experience, detail-oriented individual who takes ownership of projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to extract, analyze, and review data and make appropriate recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast paced, informal, and often ambiguous environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn and ability to quickly acquire knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously or within a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An advanced degree.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in technology, payments, or financial services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a high-growth, rapidly scaling environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A willingness to work with a diverse crew of tax nerds who care deeply about Stripe’s tax issues and each other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the realm of technological disruption, the calculation, collection and filing of indirect taxes stand as a classic challenge. Businesses operating in the US and internationally grapple with diverse tax rates and rules, nexus obligations, and registration and filing requirements. This landscape is dynamic, with frequent rule changes and potential legal consequences for inaccurate tax calculations and filings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Addressing this challenge head-on, we introduced Stripe Tax as a cutting-edge SaaS product in 2021. Our US and Global Tax Content Teams spearhead the management of global tax content that fuels Stripe Tax.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we continue to grow, we are seeking an Indirect Tax Research &amp;amp; Operations Specialist to support and grow the U.S. tax content powering the Stripe Tax engine, and to act as subject matter expert for all U.S. indirect tax matters related to the behaviors of the Stripe Tax solution.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor indirect tax developments and conduct tax research across the United States at all jurisdiction levels to support the accuracy of existing tax content powering Stripe Tax solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct tax research that drives product expansion into new industry segments and new tax types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create requirements depicting tax rates and rules, place of supply logic and economic nexus obligations for a wide range of products and services across multiple US indirect tax types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create requirements depicting tax functional behaviors supporting Stripe Tax product initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy and validate tax content updates across certain Stripe Tax systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with drafting and maintaining both internal and user-facing tax product documentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide subject matter expertise to a variety of teams including Product, Sales, Engineering, Operations, Marketing, and other business and technical teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of relevant working experience in indirect tax within a multinational, tax engine vendor, or professional consulting organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bachelor’s degree or academic equivalent in law, accounting, economics or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A focus on in-depth legal research, and the ability to simplify complex legal tax issues, making them accessible to a broad audience with varying levels of expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work remotely and independently in a high pressure environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, self-motivated, and detail oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong tax technical background with the ability to advise on tax technology and automation solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Post-graduate degree in tax or related field and/or professional qualification (CPA, JD or equivalent, Masters in Tax, or LLM or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of leading indirect tax technology and end-to-end compliance practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with leading tax automation solutions (Vertex, Avalara, Sovos, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe&#39;s infrastructure and suite of APIs powers hundreds of thousands of businesses—from startups to Fortune 500s—in almost every country around the world. From developers and product managers to founders and CFOs, a broad audience interacts with Stripe&#39;s products and uses them to start, run, and scale their companies. Removing the barriers to online commerce helps more new businesses get started, expedites growth for existing companies, and increases economic output and trade globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate at a significant scale, but we&#39;re still emerging relative to the opportunity ahead, so there is still much to do. Join us and help put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Americas Marketing team is a high-performing group laser-focused on fueling Stripe&#39;s expansion across the region. You&#39;ll have the opportunity to make a significant impact by building and optimizing programs and strategies. You&#39;ll collaborate closely with cross-functional partners in Sales, Product, Partnerships, and others to drive measurable business results and growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;responsibilities&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and oversee the regional industry marketing strategy and execution plan to fuel pipeline growth with the enterprise sales teams across the Americas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the industry GTM team to develop and execute targeted marketing strategies that align with business goals for various industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Demand Generation, Product Marketing, Sales, Customer Success, and Partnerships teams to develop and execute integrated marketing campaigns (digital, events, content, and direct outreach) that resonate with enterprise clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with sales teams to understand customer needs and tailor marketing approaches for effective engagement at the ground level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Product Marketing and GTM leads to develop compelling marketing content (brochures, presentations, case studies, blogs) that effectively communicate our value proposition to enterprise industry stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and execute industry-specific events (both Stripe-led and 3P events &amp;amp; industry conferences) to showcase our solutions and foster relationships with net-new prospects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own key business metrics and analyze and report on marketing campaign performance, utilizing data-driven insights to refine future initiatives and improve ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product management, customer success, and sales teams to ensure consistent messaging and a unified approach to the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage budgets for campaigns and events, ensuring optimal allocation of resources to achieve marketing goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage Stripe&#39;s marketing tech stack and analytics capabilities to drive data-driven decision-making and optimize the field marketing engine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a marketing thought leader representing the Americas as we build Stripe&#39;s industry strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking an experienced, creative, and results-oriented marketer who knows the enterprise audience to drive world-class industry marketing in the Americas region. If you have a proven track record for driving customer outcomes and can effectively work with sales to translate business needs into engagement opportunities; if you are someone who thrives in ambiguity, takes big swings, and comes with a growth mindset, then we want to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the industry marketing leader, you will play a pivotal role in aligning our marketing strategies with the specific dynamics of our target industries. You will be the link between product marketing and field marketing and you will partner closely with GTM to define, build, and execute on industry marketing strategies for Stripe that drive perception, engagement and ultimately revenue growth. As a member of the Americas Marketing team, this is a great opportunity to build and have a significant impact on our rapidly growing business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;minimum-requirements&quot;&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, or a related field; MBA is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in B2B marketing, preferably within an enterprise setting and in specific industry verticals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of developing and executing successful scaled and targeted multi-channel marketing campaigns across the full funnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the B2B buying process and enterprise sales cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to craft compelling messages for diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in marketing automation tools, CRM software (Salesforce), and analytics platforms (Tableau).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in both digital and in-person event environments, with a deep understanding of how to integrate event experiences into the buyer&#39;s journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful track record of collaborating with Sales teams, including joint planning, lead management, and earning trust as a strategic partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and data-driven decision-making skills with ability to synthesize and communicate business health with leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibits a strategic mindset with a strong analytical capability; comfortable with data interpretation and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build relationships and collaborate effectively across various teams and departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe builds the most powerful and flexible tools for running an internet business. We handle billions of dollars each year and enable hundreds of thousands of users around the world to scale faster and more efficiently by building their businesses on Stripe. The majority of US internet users have purchased something from a Stripe user in the past year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe’s Professional Services team works with our most strategic users; Integration Engineers lead technical workstreams with these users while they are onboarding and expanding with Stripe. We’re seeking candidates with strong technical and business skills to drive high quality integrations while accelerating the time to go-live process. You’ll work closely with cross-functional teams to drive product improvements, solve challenging and complex problems, and improve Stripe’s offerings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Own and drive relationships with external audiences of all kinds, from engineers to CTOs, to understand business objectives and translate requirements into integrations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead users through technical implementations of products across the Stripe portfolio&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Integrate Stripe’s APIs to explore new products and features&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Review and validate integrations using Stripe APIs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Advise and document best practices around integrations using Stripe APIs, Stripe products, payments, authorizations and optimizations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work closely with Stripe Product &amp;amp; Engineering teams to improve and evolve Stripe products&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Contribute to the development of Professional Services methodologies and tools to accelerate engagements and ease troubleshooting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus,&amp;nbsp; not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At least 5+ years of experience, with a strong technical generalist and coding background.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Has at least 2 years of production-level software developer experience with fluency in at least 2 programming languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Has at least 3 years of customer-facing experience working as a customer success engineer, integration engineer, solution architect, technical consultant, software engineer or similar role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Can read, write, and understand code in multiple programming languages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Has experience integrating Stripe or other RESTful APIs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;A great verbal and written communicator, strong presentation skills, comfortable explaining complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Superior time management skills to manage multiple external customers simultaneously&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Self-starter with the ability to assess, troubleshoot and work autonomously to decompose and solve complex problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Able to accommodate light travel quarterly for customer on-sites and team meetings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
