&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in designing and delivering training and awareness programs to promote risk and compliance understanding across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to establish and track metrics to measure the effectiveness of financial crimes procedures and compliance initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in policy gap assessments to ensure alignment with evolving regulatory requirements and industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills with a keen eye for detail and a process-oriented mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple projects, priorities, and deadlines in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to present complex issues clearly to senior leadership and cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
