&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Processing Cost Accounting Team is responsible for supporting all processing costs incurred by Stripe, consulting on accounting implications across global partnerships and supporting Stripe’s ability to make informed strategic decisions. Our dynamic team is expanding, and we’re looking for an experienced accountant to support our goals of scaling for the future. We operate in a fast-paced environment and collaborate significantly with cross-functional and international teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is seeking an Accounting leader to join its world class Accounting team and help us scale for the future, in a fast-paced environment that’s growing rapidly. In this role you will help stand up a robust process around accounting’s interactions with global partnership programs, designed to manage risk, influence stakeholders and evolve with new requirements. In addition, you will support our financial, regulatory and internal reporting processes, financial systems, and related internal controls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable accounting processes to support global growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the lead Accounting partner to our global partnerships teams to ensure all accounting requirements are identified, planned for and implemented for Stripe’s partner and project launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize partner launch strategies and quickly identify impact and requirements focused on costs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain accounting policies and procedural documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce internal management analyses and reporting focused on global partnerships developments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with teams such as Partnerships, Finance and Strategy, Engineering, Product, and Legal to determine and operationalize the accounting implications of new business initiatives and transaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and execute efficient internal control procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of relevant public accounting and/or industry experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B.A. or B.S degree in Accounting or Finance (CPA strongly preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in U.S. GAAP and ability to research complex accounting issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and organizational skills, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solution-oriented mindset with enthusiasm for establishing best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate and influence across diverse groups and levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of thought leadership in evolving, ambiguous areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-orientation with rigorous approach to delivering high-quality work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm to get things done through a combination of hands on execution and leading others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of (or experience in) the technology or payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Excel and experience working with large data sets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using SQL to self-service information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

