&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting, Accounting &amp;amp; Data Services is the throughline of nearly every core product Stripe offers. It’s a new and fast growing org at the company, solving urgent needs for all types of merchants coming into the Stripe dashboard trying to understand the health of their business. Our design team has the unique challenge of helping define the strategy for what many reporting and accounting Stripe experiences can and should look like based on a deep understanding of the everyday needs of our merchants. These workflows touch some of the most used surfaces in the Stripe dashboard.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Reporting, Accounting, &amp;amp; Data Services, you’ll be working on a small tight-knit design team with many opportunities to collaborate and pair design. We have much to build and there are endless opportunities for high impact design leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you’ll work on a mix of new feature development and product quality improvements to our most frequently used dashboard workflows. You’ll collaborate with product and engineering partners across several different teams to shape and execute a range of design solutions for our merchant users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand user workflows and pain points, and produce, test and iterate on high quality designs to solve user needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with product, engineering, marketing and strategy partners to define a north star and product experience for new features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prototype user experiences for testing and internal communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with teams across Stripe to craft a seamless dashboard user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct UXR to test design decisions before shipping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our design systems teams to leverage and improve page templates and components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has 4+ years relevant design experience at a product-driven tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has strong craft demonstrated through a portfolio of work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has experience designing data-rich UX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has experience collaborating closely with engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has experience collaborating with different partners across org lines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has a passion for turning complexity into usable, beautiful experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are a strong design leader comfortable with bringing your point of view to a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is investing in building out its Production Design team to reach users across the globe. This role is part of the Stripe Delivery Center (SDC),which aims to provide operational leverage and expand Stripe’s capabilities to meet the needs of both external users and internal teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ad Design:&lt;/strong&gt; We design comprehensive ad campaigns tailored for various platforms, ensuring that every visual element aligns with our marketing goals and engages our audience effectively.&amp;nbsp; We localize our content to meet the unique cultural and linguistic needs of different regions. This team will be responsible for adapting our visuals to effectively present our message in local languages.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graphic Design for Presentations:&lt;/strong&gt; In addition to our work in advertising and web content, we also produce highly crafted presentations aimed at large users and executive audiences. Our design work enhances the clarity and impact of our messages, making complex information accessible and engaging. Whether it&#39;s a pitch to clients or a strategy meeting with executives, we provide visually compelling presentations that communicate our ideas confidently and effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a talented and versatile Production Design Manager to join our creative team. The primary responsibility of this role is to own the production process and team that adapts and updates existing ad creatives. Your team will be responsible for generating new variations of ad creatives with a high bar for quality. You will work closely with the marketing and creative teams to ensure the seamless execution of visual assets, delivering them on schedule and at high quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow and develop a team of production design associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the production schedule: ensure the team is able to turn around design briefs within SLA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a strong strategic acumen for developing complex program roadmaps and XFN process in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project management through documentation, tooling, trackers, standing meetings, org-wide updates, and Slack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven excellence in producing creative systems that are optimized for scale and growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold high quality standards: ensure that all ad creatives adhere to established brand guidelines, visual standards, and size/format requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the key point of contact for creative and marketing teams to improve the process, increase velocity, improve quality and provide a feedback loop on any challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for automation and process improvement through adopting or building tools for design associates and marketers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Figma, Adobe Creative Cloud, and Google apps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all assets follow best practices for file organization, asset management, and version control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a keen eye for detail and ensure that all deliverables are of the highest quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-4 years of experience in a production design management or similar role (team lead or manager), in either an agency or in-house role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in design production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Talented at coaching and developing production designers: this role involves building a new team and capability that doesn’t exist today.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert in Adobe Creative Cloud (Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign), Figma, Canva, Frame and Google Slides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent eye for detail and strong understanding of layout, typography, and color theory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams and adapt to changing project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong time management and organizational skills to juggle multiple tasks and meet tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with different digital ad formats, ad specs and best practices of design for different ad platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for staying up-to-date with design trends and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While accepting payments on the internet has gotten easier over the past several years due in large part to the advent of modern payments APIs, the internet infrastructure for routing these same payments (to suppliers, sellers, partners, service providers, recipients) is stuck in the stone-age.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect is Stripe’s leading product for marketplaces, on-demand services, ecommerce site builders, invoicing platforms, professional SaaS products, fundraising platforms, rental management platforms, and more. By utilizing the power of Connect, users in each of these categories can link multiple parties for the exchange of goods or services. These users rely on Connect for the crucial function of reliably routing payments between these parties.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By powering fast, flexible, compliant, and cost-efficient routing of payments on the internet, Connect not only spurs the creation of innovative business models but it also enables organizations (whether they are businesses, nonprofits, or governmental agencies) to channel previously-offline payments to the internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Lead on the Connect team at Stripe, you will be devising strategy, developing product requirements, and overseeing execution for some of the highest impact initiatives that serve modern marketplaces and software platforms.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Stripe, Product Managers help build innovative payments products for our customers. Product development is an extremely collaborative effort between engineering, design, analytics and customer-facing teams. You’d be joining a team of experienced Product Managers who have a track record of successfully building large-scale business and consumer products that are collectively impacting millions of users around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a day to day basis you would spend your time split between external meetings with customers and internal discussions with your engineering, marketing, analytics, and sales counterparts; as well as with your direct reports, coaching, mentoring, and hiring. This role will provide the opportunity to develop the strategy for one of Stripe’s core products and get feedback on your plans directly from Stripe’s leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the product roadmap for our core Connect product&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devise strategy, steer product requirements, and oversee execution for some of the highest impact initiatives that serve modern marketplaces &amp;amp; software platforms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross functionally with engineering, design, analytics, and other global teams to define, build, and deploy products that delight our users&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the GTM strategy that maximizes customer impact and learnings, while minimizing risk&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and coach your team on best practices in defining product requirements and how to deliver against those requirements and the overall roadmap&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of managing product managers, 8+ years as a product manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading cross-team initiatives from ideation to execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical expertise: You’ve led technical products and/or have a background in computer science (or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building both new products (0-&amp;gt;1) as well as a track record of shipping continuous product improvements to an existing product portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep user empathy and a high bar for user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Persistence and a whatever-it-takes approach to ensure that your product is successful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on a platform and/or marketplace product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on a paytech/fintech product&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Lead, Financial Risk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Financial Risk teams focus on detecting and taking action on different types of financial risk vectors that Stripe faces in processing payments for millions of businesses. For example, we work on detecting and offboarding fraudulent accounts, designing new ways to separate good businesses from malicious actors, as well as monitoring the credit risk and profitability of our merchant portfolio. We operate at the intersection of technology and finance, deploying a complex set of automated systems, including machine learning models, to efficiently manage Risk at scale with global reach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As PM lead for Financial Risk, in particular Fraud and Credit, you will be responsible for defining and executing the product strategy for deterring Fraud and optimizing our approach to Credit Risk management. You will manage a team of exceptional product managers that are responsible for building out the end-to-end systems we use to mitigate Financial Risk and protect Stripe, while ensuring a great user experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, coach, and manage PMs in the Financial Risk (Fraud and Credit Risk) team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the goals and multi-year product roadmap for Fraud &amp;amp; Credit Risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand and articulate how our users interact with these systems and how to ensure a great user experience while protecting Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboratively partner with other Stripe teams early in the product development lifecycle and jointly shape product plans that lead with delightful risk experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the delivery of delightful user experiences by collaborating with the many internal teams responsible for Stripe’s risk and compliance management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data analysis skills and familiarity in working with probabilistic systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product sense, including experience building both business and consumer experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Machine Learning teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing a multi-year vision, strategy and roadmap for large scale products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A capacity to build team vision, hire outperformers, and lead a high performing team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to turn incomplete, conflicting, or ambiguous inputs into solid action plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to communicate well to the broader organization; setting a compelling vision and with a talent for precise articulations of customer problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to work closely with users, gather feedback, and understand their problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of product management experience, 5+ years managing a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical skills e.g., ability to gain an in-depth understanding of software systems, build a robust integration with the Stripe API, make meaningful contributions to high-stakes discussions on data modeling or software architecture, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strongly preferred: Have experience with Machine Learning and/or a background in a computational science / mathematics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

