&lt;p&gt;The Seller Experience &amp;amp; Insights team is responsible for ensuring GTM (Go-To-Market) has the optimal tools, systems and processes in place to effectively sell at Stripe. We transform, improve and support global Stripe Go-To-Market teams tooling and business processes to drive productivity and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a self-starter to join our team who has demonstrated success dealing with ambiguous global-scale initiatives, with multi-layered stakeholder management and significant cross-functional team engagement. This role will focus on improving the GTM tools, systems and processes in collaboration with cross functional teams, including Engineering, Data Science and Finance. You will drive operational rigor through KPIs, regular collaborative progress reviews, and continuous communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and establish key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure the success of go-to-market tools and processes, regularly reviewing them for relevance and effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a centralized system to collect insights and identify friction points from sellers, collaborating with cross-functional teams to implement effective solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess the impact of tool and process changes on seller performance and satisfaction, analyzing key metrics (e.g., sales performance, tool usage rates, and seller satisfaction scores) to drive continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead initiatives to optimize seller tools and processes (e.g., Salesforce, Ironclad, Tableau) to enhance efficiency and effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal communications and operations teams to design and execute change management plans, ensuring new processes and tools are effectively communicated and adopted by sellers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales Enablement on implementing new tools or processes for go-to-market sales teams, ensuring minimal disruption for sellers during transitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in sales, program management, or process improvement, preferably in an e-commerce or technology environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience building or supporting GTM processes, workflows, data and systems, including Salesforce and other Sales productivity tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive mindset with a high degree of comfort navigating ambiguity and rapidly changing priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to seamlessly transition from strategy, high level to very detailed, and a willingness to “roll up your sleeves”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to simplify, structure, and diagnose problems and with a high degree of comfort working quickly in a high growth, fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, presentation, and communication experience, influencing across all levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, presentation, and communication skills, with the ability to influence at all levels of the organization—from frontline teams to executive leadership, and synthesize detailed information into clear, actionable strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build strong executive relationships to create clarity and context around key decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with cross-functional teams to implement workflows and processes that support user engagement and satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, capable of influencing key stakeholders and engaging with sellers effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong ability to empathize with seller challenges and effectively diagnose underlying issues affecting their experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort operating with incomplete or varying data, demonstrating adaptability in prioritizing activities based on shifting business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive problem-solving and analytical experience, particularly in addressing operational or competitive challenges in a sales-oriented environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with process improvement methodologies, such as Lean Six Sigma, is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for continuous learning and improvement for yourself and your team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in sales or process architecture roles is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally located in NYC, or on the East Coast&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recruiting team seeks to build the culture of Stripe by aligning the strongest global talent to our highest impact business needs. They focus on bringing Stripe’s operating principles to life in their recruiting processes, providing the highest-quality candidate experience, and leveraging data driven storytelling to influence the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To further this important mission, we are looking for consultative and creative recruiters to grow and scale our Go-to-Market (GTM) team and Stripe Delivery Center in Mexico City. The Stripe Delivery Center is a new global team with the purpose of building Stripe’s operations capabilities for the next decade. Our GTM team is established globally but expanding in the region, and focuses on bringing new users onto the Stripe platform, supporting our existing users&#39; scale, and growing their businesses.&amp;nbsp;As a recruiter, you will be helping us hire for these teams in Mexico City, looking for dynamic and curious people who have a passion for solving global user issues, building user facing or operations teams and who want to play a front-line role in building this new operational capability for Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can expect high impact and wide-ranging responsibilities: owning full-cycle recruiting, driving hiring strategy, and delivering best-in-class candidate experience. This person must be a builder who thrives in a learning environment—unafraid to try new things, embrace new ideas, and welcome suggestions for how we can iterate on our processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior leaders across the organization to understand their hiring objectives and develop team recruiting strategies to hit headcount goals, with a focus on building our GTM and Operations teams in Mexico City&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help initiate creative and scalable changes to our existing recruiting strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze metrics; report on hiring progress to business leadership on a regular cadence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Concentrate on creating strategic plans for sourcing candidates with diverse backgrounds for each of your roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams like Finance, People Ops, Benefits, Onboarding and Legal to deliver a high-quality and holistic candidate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of full-cycle Recruiting experience in a fast-paced, high-growth environment including in house experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including business proficiency in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven abilities to attract passive candidates and build a diverse pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An active and data driven approach to problem solving; you enjoy making sense of the trends and using the insights to better your process to make it more efficient&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for building teams and delivering exceptional candidate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growth mindset and truly flexible; you can shift tasks and priorities when circumstances change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in working in a cross-functional and fluid environment with the ability to learn quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To further this important mission, we are looking for a consultative and creative Recruiter to join us and work with Stripe to grow and scale our teams. You can expect high impact and wide-ranging responsibility: owning full-cycle recruiting, driving hiring strategy, leading first-in-kind searches, and delivering best-in-class candidate experience. This person must be a builder who thrives in a learning environment—unafraid to try new things, embrace new ideas, and welcome suggestions for how we can iterate on our processes. This is a 11 month fixed-term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior leaders across the organization to understand their hiring objectives and develop team recruiting strategies to hit headcount goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help initiate creative and scalable changes to our existing recruiting strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze metrics and report on hiring progress to business leadership on a regular cadence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Concentrate on creating strategic plans for sourcing candidates with diverse backgrounds for each of your roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams like Finance, People Ops, Benefits, Onboarding and Legal to deliver a high-quality and holistic candidate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of full-cycle Business, Technical and/or General Recruiting experience in a fast-paced, high-growth environment including in house experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with an appropriate blend of professionalism and friendliness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven abilities to attract passive senior candidates and build a diverse pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An active and data driven approach to problem solving; you enjoy making sense of the trends and using the insights to better your process to make it more efficient&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for building teams and delivering exceptional candidate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growth mindset and truly flexible. You can shift tasks and priorities when circumstances change (at a fast-growing startup, they often do)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in working in a cross-functional and fluid environment, the ability to learn quickly, and no desire to take yourself too seriously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Recruiting Program Management Team supports Stripe’s Recruiting Team through the implementation of various projects and programs designed to optimize for the caliber and productivity of Stripe’s Recruiting organization. Responsibilities include leading high-priority projects to improve operational efficiency, driving cornerstone programmatic offerings, influencing data-driven decision-making, and guiding change management. We are looking for a talented program manager to join our team to support (1) Operations Recruiting and (2) Centralized Recruiting Programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the directly responsible individual (DRI) for one centralized recruiting program, such as Recruiter Enablement, Hiring Manager Enablement, etc. As DRI:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the program’s annual goals (tracking, reporting, program-managing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide enablement to any users of the program: recruiters, hiring managers, interviewers, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain any knowledge articles about the program to ensure accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for operational improvements across recruiting programs and processes to keep them as effective and efficient as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop calibration and assessment rubrics, training guides, and educational content for all program participants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the program manager supporting the Operations Recruiting pillar. Support the Operations Recruiting org on a variety of initiatives, including, but not limited to:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Global Recruiting Lead(s) and Recruiting Managers to identify and execute high-priority initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successfully execute centralized recruiting programs at the local level in the pillar you support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and lead recruiting-focused projects to support our hiring teams and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional projects by facilitating communication, coordination, planning and execution across the recruiting team and partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage data to define program success metrics and inform strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a positive candidate experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively share data-centric updates with stakeholders to maintain aligned decision making and build trusted partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management efforts across our recruiting teams and partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to other business-critical Recruiting initiatives as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Functional experience in recruiting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with program, change, and project management in a fast-paced, high-growth environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for building new and inclusive programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong initiative, autonomy, critical thinking skills, and an eye for the details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven abilities to think creatively and build from scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An active and data-driven approach to problem solving; you enjoy making sense of trends and using insights to improve your work and environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability and a growth mindset; you can shift tasks and priorities with circumstances change&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability and willingness to attend to work matters outside normal business hours on an as-needed basis (this role supports a global team, so flexibility to adjust your working schedule to connect with counterparts in different time zones is preferable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Risk and Reward team is responsible for managing the end-to-end risk strategy for all business processing payments on Stripe. We are responsible for developing innovative and tailored strategies to minimize both credit and fraud risk while ensuring the best user experience on the platform. The Global team is composed of curious, driven, and analytical individuals who are passionate about using their skills to shape the future of Stripe. We partner closely with Stripe&#39;s sales, engineering, data science, product, and servicing teams to leverage existing platforms, integrate industry best practices, and develop novel solutions to evaluate and manage risk. If you are interested in joining a fast-growing organization and applying your experience to shape the future of Stripe, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the APAC Risk Lead, you will be responsible for overseeing and enhancing Stripe’s risk management strategies across the region. You will be the subject matter expert on the regional risk landscape, including regulatory requirements and emerging trends. Your role will involve collaborating with various teams—such as sales, product, engineering, data science, compliance, and other functions—to ensure that risk initiatives are effectively implemented and aligned across the organization. Additionally, you will build and maintain relationships with external stakeholders, such as merchants, financial partners and regulators to strengthen our risk management practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone with a strategic mindset and a passion for driving innovation in risk management while ensuring that we maintain the highest standards for our users and partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement tailored risk management strategies that aligns with company goals and adapts to the dynamic regulatory landscape and market conditions in various APAC countries, including designing product solutions to scalably manage risks in line with these strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish region-specific risk policies and governance frameworks that reflect local nuances and comply with legal requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with cross-functional teams to gather insights, improve our risk assessment methods, and ensure smooth collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with growth teams to influence product roadmaps. Design and execute effective growth strategies that align with risk management objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement robust business and operational systems and processes to ensure that risk management scales effectively with Stripe’s evolving needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present comprehensive regional risk reports to leadership, highlighting local risk factors and developments to inform strategic decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote a culture of risk awareness and accountability throughout the APAC organization, ensuring that all employees understand and embrace their role in effective risk management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and nurture a diverse, high-performing risk management team with expertise in regional complexities, fostering professional growth and collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate would ideally have worked within the context of enabling cross-border money movement and/or embedded finance for businesses, and is knowledgeable of the regulatory &amp;amp; compliance requirements across the region. A strong candidate will be comfortable navigating highly ambiguous, complex, and cross-functional projects in fast-paced working environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 12 years of experience in risk management, preferably within payments or consumer banking, or in a role that demands deep expertise in payments and consumer risk issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in developing and implementing effective risk management strategies across various domains, including credit, fraud, compliance, and brand risk, particularly within the APAC region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building strong cross-functional partnerships with sales, product, engineering, partnerships, and legal teams, fostering collaboration and alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with experience presenting complex, strategic initiatives to senior business leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of managing a rapidly growing team in a high-growth environment, showcasing skills in recruiting, mentoring, and guiding high-performing individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Mandarin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at addressing ambiguous challenges and defining strategies that clarify objectives, drive alignment, and yield measurable business impact for Stripe’s users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing payments risk related to cross-border businesses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple stakeholders with varying priorities and drive creative solutions and commitment to a shared goal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise with quantitative tools such as Python, R, or Stata&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Who we are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Sales Development Manager at Stripe, you will drive Stripe’s future growth engine by leading a team of inbound and/or outbound SDRs. You will be working with the Stripe’s Sales teams to build Stripe’s sales pipeline. As a Sales Development manager, you’ll lead and coach a group of high-performing SDRs, helping them deliver on ambitious targets, as well as roll up your sleeves to work directly with the team. We are looking for a self-starter who has demonstrated success dealing with ambiguity, operating in a high-growth environment, and solving problems with limited oversight. Ideal candidates will have management experience scaling a technology Sales Development team and superior communication skills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We take a data-driven, analytical approach to Sales Development, and are looking for someone who enjoys building – who will actively participate in the development of sales processes, the articulation of Stripe’s value proposition, and the creation of key tools and assets to measure success. Stripe is not a typical company, and this is not a typical sales development function. If you’re hungry, smart, persistent, and a great teammate, we want to hear from you!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the team - Recruit, train and lead a rapidly growing team of SDRs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to both the long-term vision and strategy for the team and manage day-to-day operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, own and execute a pipeline strategy for the market you’ll support. This role will operate with a degree of autonomy and will require strong strategic thinking ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive execution of Stripe’s new business pipeline goals by understanding and analyzing top of the funnel metrics, pipeline quality, and revenue influenced across different segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach, mentor and guide the team in developing consultative and solution-based sales skills including: campaign strategy, outbound execution, and nurturing interest in opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape deep partnerships with Marketing, Sales, Sales Operations, Enablement, and Product Marketing teams to successfully collaborate on campaigns and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize your business for efficiency, accelerating ramp time to productivity, and ensure your team has a crisp understanding of Stripe domain knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively work cross-functionally across the organization to shape Stripe&#39;s solutions to meet client needs, working with partners based in different locations and time zones.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire, motivate and enable individual development to promote career growth of direct reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of people management experience (or equivalent to relevant experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in building teams with a strong network across the countries you’ll support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven understanding of APAC and EMEA regions. Ability to lead a team that will support global markets. Including countries across APAC and EMEA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading inbound/ outbound sales and operations in an early stage, high-growth technology environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of high performance in a pipeline generating or closing role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to create and execute a pipeline strategy for the country you’ll be leading.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
