&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Help us scale our global security team!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is looking for an experienced Regional Security Manager to join our team. As the Regional Security Manager Americas at Stripe, you will be responsible for developing our core physical security deliverables to office locations in the Americas (North America and parts of Latin America), and help evolve our program to support Stripe around the globe. You will work cross functionally within the Corporate Security team, and alongside other business teams at the company to keep Stripe secure and Stripes safe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a leader on the team reporting to the Head of Global Security Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and provide oversight of our physical security operations function in the Americas region and support the wider team globally as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Stripe&#39;s business leads, workplace teams and external business partners to optimize the team to scale with business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, review, and refine policy and procedure guidance documents for security practices, user operations escalations, event management, crisis management, and incident documentation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with functional, business and vendor teams across the company to conduct risk, threat and vulnerability assessments to identify and document Stripe&#39;s most impactful risks. Recommend and deploy appropriate mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively manage services providers, ensuring an effective risk based programs operating within a developed set of standard operating procedures. Provide feedback through service level agreements, quarterly business reviews and agreed key performance indicators.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forecast budgets accurately, make improvement and cost-efficiency suggestions and manage operations to budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and administer employee education programming to increase security awareness levels throughout the regional offices as we continue to develop a culture of security that protects Stripe and our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with business continuity, crisis management and environmental, health &amp;amp; safety teams to ensure emergency incident and crisis response plans are in place and tested regularly.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide security design expertise and project management in relation to new office builds and expansion efforts throughout the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spearhead the planning and execution of proactive, innovative security programs and projects to reduce risk to Stripe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5+ years experience working at a multinational company, with responsibility for regional security operations in the Americas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold a degree in a security or risk related field and/or be certified through ASIS International with a CPP or similar designation that demonstrates an active interest and desire to continually develop in your professional field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid understanding of core physical security risks and threats, and experience in developing effective and measurable programs in an international setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strategic mindset with a service attitude, constantly working towards satisfying the needs of our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a great communicator and solid project manager, able to effectively prioritize and advance a large number of projects happening simultaneously, often on tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A highly developed network of resources, cultivated through years of building relationships in the security industry, government and the tech community to ensure your effectiveness in a wide region with complex geopolitical, cultural, and business environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extreme organizational skills, hyper-responsiveness, and leadership excellence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to travel internationally (when restrictions allow) up to 25% of the time, sometimes at short notice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in proactively and collaboratively assessing and mitigating organizational risks and challenges to deliver successful outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner Risk Operations (PRO) is responsible for managing the risk relationships spanning across global payment method, card, and financial partners. It is our mission to build operational controls to mitigate user and partner risk and enable strategic development opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Risk Operations Analyst you will be working to ensure our policies, operations, and workflows align to the needs of our financial partners You will be accountable for workflows impacting a variety of cross-functional internal and external stakeholders to identify and assess regulatory, contractual, and partner risk. Further, you will influence and advise operational teams in building out scalable operational processes to ensure compliance with service level agreements, routine reporting, and overall risk mitigation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate sound judgment and an ability to navigate non-binary, high-risk decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate merchants, from successful venture-backed startups to well established institutions, by assessing suitability to process on Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere closely to process while still constantly questioning assumptions, suggesting improvements, and balancing user experience with compliance requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively and clearly communicate with other Stripes, Stripe&#39;s users, and Stripe&#39;s financial partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify trends and further report these to cross functional teams to enhance detection systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to projects to enhance and optimize due diligence strategy systems and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build and scale processes across the risk operations eco-system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in current systems, policies and strategies, and recommend enhancements and process improvements to mitigate emerging risks through a collaborative approach with stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2+ years of experience in risk management, compliance, or financial operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep empathy for entrepreneurs running a business, and are motivated to solve problems to empower them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability and desire to challenge the status quo&lt;/li&gt;
