&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s (Startups + Small and Medium Businesses) SSMB Solutions Architecture (SA) team works with technical and business leaders (CTO/ CIO/ CEO/ Founders etc.), payments leaders and product engineering teams in the mid-market segment to evangelize Stripe’s solutions in the market. A solutions architect’s role is to build relationships with decision makers and think strategically about the business needs of Stripe’s customers. Solution Architects identify and propose Stripe solutions to solve complex business challenges and drive growth for our customers. SSMB SAs establish and prescribe best practices around a customer’s strategy, provide business and technical thought leadership and are viewed as a trusted advisor. They work on scaling business processes aligned to maximizing account coverage while working closely with customer and partner resources to deliver a solution that can be adopted quickly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the team, the Solutions Architect will build highly consultative trusted relationships with c-level executives and technical decision makers in the customer’s organization to provide business and technical thought leadership, and become a trusted advisor in solving mission-critical business challenges. She/he will architect business models with them so they can drive new monetization opportunities and growth for both the user and Stripe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive thought leadership and build executive relationships with key business and technical stakeholders including CIO, CTO, COO, CRO, CDO &amp;amp; Head of Payments. Strive to become their trusted advisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work to deeply understand the customer’s business objectives and apply Stripe’s payments, SaaS, Banking-as-a-Service and Link Network solutions to customer challenges&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Secure the technical win for Stripe’s products by delivering demos, responding to RFPs, evangelizing Stripe’s products, and collaborating internally on narratives that align with the customer’s goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating scalable processes (1:M customer engagements, Webinars, office hours etc), partnerships (with external and internal partners) and scaled assets (reusable videos/ templates) in order to act as a force-multiplier in the sales process.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand Stripe’s footprint within existing accounts to new global markets and business units by introducing new capabilities and local payment methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with multiple internal stakeholders including go-to-market, product and marketing to deliver impactful EBC briefings for SSMB accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of the customer to inform our product team on insights, trends, and opportunities across our SSMB accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with professional services and partners to accelerate activations and time to live&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with partners to help Stripe scale and reach its Total Addressable Market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approximately 25% travel is anticipated to help you connect in-person in a meaningful way with users and collaborate internally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An ideal candidate should have experience working for medium to large&amp;nbsp; software companies (preferably in In payment-tech), focused on identifying business priorities, technology strategy, and solution design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will have demonstrated the ability to become a trusted advisor to senior executives and facilitate customer success including business value identification(discovery/ demo cycles), road mapping, as well as advising and defining successful execution strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideal candidates have external customer-facing experience, have payment expertise (preferred but not required) who can present and architect Stripe’s solutions, and persuade decision makers to leverage Stripe technology to drive business value. Candidates have previous experience in web architecture, enterprise architecture or experience defining and optimizing financial business processes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in a similar customer-facing engineering role (e.g. solutions architect, sales engineer, customer success, professional services delivery) for a fin-tech/payment-tech / global software enterprise with 5+ years of total relevant experience (software development, enterprise sales/ architecture, business development etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a customer facing roles - presenting and architecting solutions. Domain experience in the payments space is preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding or background in writing code in at least 2 of Stripe’s primary deployment languages (Ruby, Python, JavaScript, Java, Go, etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding oral and written communication skills, presentation skills, and comfortable explaining complex concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able and willing to learn Stripe solutions (Payments, Billing, Connect, etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability&amp;nbsp; to understand how a wide variety of technologies and systems interact with each other (ERP, CRM, Billing, Tax, Legacy)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive engagement skills and presence, with an ability to establish strong relationships with key decision makers and build credibility at all levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational/time management skills and the ability to juggle competing priorities while working with multiple opportunities and customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills to work seamlessly with the broader GTM team to support our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience solving open ended business problems with a combination of technology and creative thinking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel per business needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who We Are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About The Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialist Solutions Architects (SSA) are domain experts aligned to specific Stripe solutions and customer buying centers. We have in-depth knowledge of specific solution offerings and understanding of customer’s challenges. We align with specialized product sellers on deals, advise the broader pre-sales team on complex opportunities, support pipeline development and revenue attainment, serve as an advisor on go-to-market sales plays, and provide critical insights to our product and engineering teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will collaborate closely with sales and pre-sales teams to drive pipeline and revenue targets, while also educating the product and engineering teams on market trends and strongly influencing the product roadmap. You will develop deep relationships with senior customer business leaders and grow Stripe’s solution offerings with new and existing customers. As subject matter experts, you will scale the broader organization by delivering training, creating reusable assets, and coaching others on complex high-value opportunities. You will also run customer workshops and take lead on some key opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a Subject Matter Expert on Stripe’s Tax product to accelerate opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a deep understanding of global indirect taxes and how an automated compliance solution can help online businesses with their VAT, GST, sales tax and other compliance requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide solutions and recommendations to different business models (B2C, B2B and platforms) and industries on how to integrate with Stripe Tax to be compliant with indirect taxes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct deep discovery of customers’ current processes and needs to architect an elegant Stripe solution that can be shared with customers to drive key solution and implementation decisions that accelerate deals and activations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and share best practices and reusable assets such as reference architectures to enhance the quality and efficiency of the broader sales and pre-sales organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the product sales team and actively drive opportunities for Stripe’s largest customers by leading Tax solution strategy and own key customer relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a “Voice of the Customer” to drive product and feature request prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify product, industry, implementation and competitive trends, and provide actionable insights to product stakeholders and sales to influence Stripe’s Tax product roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an escalation point to drive our most complex technical issues to resolution with Stripe’s engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the technical health of the business on quarterly sales forecast calls and highlight any deal blockers with proposed solutions where applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support marketing events e.g. exec briefings, conferences, user groups, trade shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in a similar customer-facing engineering role such as solution consultant, solutions architect, or sales engineer, for a global software enterprise.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of accounting/indirect tax/compliance experience within a technical sales organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with/implementing a tax automation software solution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in learning and staying up to date with new indirect tax laws.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for learning and researching current and emerging products to develop innovative solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to build strong collaborative working relationships with business partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to deal effectively with ambiguity and thrive in an unstructured, fast-moving environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of software engineering and architecture patterns, with the ability to understand how a wide variety of technologies and systems interact with each other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills, comfortable explaining complex concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in solving open ended business problems with a combination of technology and creative thinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for learning and researching current and emerging products to develop innovative solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being able to do a deep dive in compliance subjects including VAT, GST, B2B Invoices, Mandatory E-Invoicing Requirements, Sales and Use Tax, Exemption Certificates and Tax IDs to help uncover a business’s indirect tax requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating Stripe or other RESTful APIs into web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with other tax solutions such as Avalara, Vertex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-Sales experience with Enterprise users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe builds the economic infrastructure for the internet. Building trust between banks, businesses &amp;amp; customers is a key ingredient for Stripe to be successful. Unfortunately, fraudsters &amp;amp; bad actors erode that trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fraud Decisions team builds decision systems to reduce fraud while retaining a best-in-class user experience. Our work directly impacts Stripe&#39;s bottom line, and we help build a safer financial backbone for the internet.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here are some of the problems you will be tackling:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design a scalable fraud decision platform with centralized backtesting, observability, experimentation, and exemption management.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create smarter decision frameworks that, in addition to fraud predictions, account for future revenues and losses in every fraud decision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a dynamic risk management layer that automatically adjusts risk parameters for cohorts of merchants in response to evolving threats and attacks - without human involvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have an outsized impact on the direction, design &amp;amp; implementation of the solutions to these problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting the technical direction and roadmap for the team to achieve business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building systems that evaluate businesses for various types of fraud, and take appropriate actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proposing new decision policies and actions that directly reduce Stripe’s fraud losses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debugging production issues across services and multiple levels of the stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping engineers across the company to develop technologies for scaling our infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 8 years of experience designing, building, and maintaining distributed systems&lt;/li&gt;
