&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See yourself at Twilio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join the team as our next Enterprise Security Engineer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &amp;amp; why we’re hiring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twilio powers real-time business communications and data solutions that help &lt;a href=&quot;https://customers.twilio.com/&quot;&gt;companies and developers worldwide&lt;/a&gt; build better applications and customer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although we&#39;re headquartered in San Francisco, we have presence throughout South America, Europe, Asia and Australia. We&#39;re on a journey to becoming a global company that actively opposes racism and all forms of oppression and bias. At Twilio, we support&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.twilio.com/company/diversity&quot;&gt;diversity, equity &amp;amp; inclusion&lt;/a&gt; wherever we do business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Entsec Engineer (P3) will be responsible for evolving and maturing Twilio’s Enterprise Security. This team has seen some significant growth in responsibilities, and we are looking for an experienced member to help bring us to the next level. This means bringing in broad enterprise security knowledge, an ability to gain technical depth quickly and ability to communicate and collaborate effectively across multiple stakeholders at once.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consult with business units to enhance security across the enterprise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work to mature a growing team and improve the team’s overall processes and capabilities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform threat modeling, architectural reviews and risk assessments to influence security best practices across enterprise solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop security standards, guidelines and policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead large projects end-to-end as a subject matter expert, bringing in industry best practices to solve complex security problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not all applicants will have skills that match a job description exactly. Twilio values diverse experiences in other industries, and we encourage everyone who meets the required qualifications to apply. While having “desired” qualifications make for a strong candidate, we encourage applicants with alternative experiences to also apply. If your career is just starting or hasn&#39;t followed a traditional path, don&#39;t let that stop you from considering Twilio. We are always looking for people who will bring something new to the table!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in information security space.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years experience in enterprise security/security engineering teams implementing and improving enterprise security platforms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with OS and endpoint security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience performing threat modeling and architectural reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in collecting and analyzing logs and other telemetry data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable subject matter expert on security issues and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with designing and implementing security best practices in cloud based IAM solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with design and implementation of Zero Trust architecture and solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SaaS application security including assessing risks and driving improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be remote, and based in Ireland or UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We prioritize connection and opportunities to build relationships with our customers and each other. For this role, you may be required to travel occasionally to participate in project or team in-person meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
