&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in leave management and accommodation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of FMLA, ADA, and other leave laws, program management and compliance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in employee education/engagement, rolling out communications and enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills and ability to maintain effective working relationships with internal &amp;amp; external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical aptitude, experience with HCM systems Workday preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in a related field or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing leave programs for large global organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of successful partnership and management of external carriers such as TPA’s, internal and external legal counsel and other providers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of monitoring and improving operations, decrease turnaround times, streamline work processes, and work collaboratively across internal teams to provide effective customer service to employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working remotely and for multinational companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize and maintain flexibility in a fast-paced, changing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail, organizational, and project management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be remote, but is not eligible to be hired in CA, CT, NJ, NY, PA, WA&lt;/p&gt;
